article.headline: UC Santa Barbara 68, UC Davis 47
article.story: SANTA BARBARA, Calif. -- James Nunnally scored 17 points and keyed a late charge to lift UC Santa Barbara past UC Davis 68-47 on Friday night. After UC Davis had cut the Gauchos' lead to 45-40, Nunnally scored eight points in a 21-4 run that put UCSB ahead 66-44 with 1:56 left. The Gauchos (7-6, 2-1 Big West) got 14 points from Jaime Serna, 12 from Orlando Johnson and 10 from James Powell. Julian Welch scored 12 for the Aggies (6-9, 2-1), who got 11 apiece from Joe Harden and Dominic Calegari. UC Santa Barbara had a major shooting advantage, hitting 28 of 49 (58.3 percent) to 17 of 43 (39.5 percent) for UC Davis. UCSB also had a 29-22 rebounding edge. After a 26-26 tie at intermission, the Gauchos opened the second half with Serna's three-point play for a 29-26 edge. The Aggies twice trimmed it to one but never led again.
